    "Reason : 1 - The proposed advertisement, by virtue of its location, scale, prominence, and method of illumination, would add visual clutter, detrimental to the amenity of the area and wider streetscene, contrary to policies D1 (Design) and D4 (Advertisements) of the Camden Local Plan 2017.\r\n",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposed advertisement, by virtue of its location, scale, orientation, prominence, and method of illumination, would introduce a distraction to traffic and pedestrians directly outside of Chalk Farm Underground Station and close to the junction of Adelaide Road and Haverstock Hill, causing harm to highway and public safety, contrary to TfL guidance, and to Local Plan Policies A1 (Managing the Impact of Development), D4 (Advertisements) and T1 (Prioritising walking, cycling and public transport)."
